                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Italy)/5–1545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Patterson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-15T21:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 15, 1945—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 16—4:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. At 6:30 tonight Stevenson and I saw Marshal Tito and presented separate notes
                    embodying message in Deptel 86, May 14. After <pb facs="1176" n="1164"
                        xml:id="pg_1164"/> reading notes, Tito said that as Yugoslav troops had
                    conquered this territory by force of arms and bloodshed, it was unfair that they
                    should not be allowed to stay on it. Yugoslavia was evidently a third class Ally
                    which did not enjoy the same rights as other classes of Allies. He had only just
                    received the British and United States notes asking him to withdraw his troops
                    from Austria (Deptel 88, May 14)<note n="49" xml:id="d1085fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1945v05#pg_1319">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p.
                            1319</ref>.</note> and now received these notes about Venezia Giulia.
                    All he could say was that he was surprised. He promised to reply tomorrow, May
                    16.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Patterson</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
